00:57:54.030 --> 00:57:57.520
The Speech Synthesis is a
single class and it can speak

00:57:57.700 --> 00:57:59.180
any string synchronously.

00:57:59.180 --> 00:58:00.010
It's really easy.

00:58:00.240 --> 00:58:02.210
It's one line.

00:58:02.270 --> 00:58:06.670
If you need asynchronous speech, that is,
you want to animate the screen

00:58:06.670 --> 00:58:09.940
or do something else in your
application while it's speaking,

00:58:09.940 --> 00:58:13.760
or you want more control,
such as highlighting words while

00:58:13.820 --> 00:58:20.850
they're spoken or doing lip syncing,
then you can set up a delegate for

00:58:20.850 --> 00:58:22.610
notification and there's a lot more
control like that that you can get.

00:58:22.820 --> 00:58:25.880
For Speech Recognition, again,
there's one class to

00:58:25.920 --> 00:58:27.460
use in the simple case.

00:58:27.460 --> 00:58:29.880
You get a shared instance of that class,
you specify which commands

00:58:29.880 --> 00:58:32.700
you want to listen to,
and then you just begin listening.

00:58:33.100 --> 00:58:37.940
This takes, does in three lines,
what in the Carbon API would

00:58:37.950 --> 00:58:42.700
take somewhere between three
and five pages of code.

